901.definition: [βαθύς] from the base of {{G939}}; profound (as going down), literally or figuratively

902.definition: [βαΐον] a diminutive of a derivative probably of the base of {{G939}}; a palm twig (as going out far)

903.definition: [Βαλαάμ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1109}}); Balaam, a Mesopotamian (symbolic of a false teacher)

904.definition: [Βαλάκ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1111}}); Balak, a Moabite

905.definition: [βαλάντιον] probably remotely from {{G906}} (as a depository); a pouch (for money)

906.definition: [βάλλω] a primary verb; to throw (in various applications, more or less violent or intense) Compare {{G4496}}.

907.definition: [βαπτίζω] from a derivative of {{G911}}; to immerse, submerge; to make whelmed (i.e. fully wet); used only (in the New Testament) of ceremonial ablution, especially (technically) of the ordinance of Christian baptism

910.definition: [Βαπτιστής] from {{G907}}; a baptizer, as an epithet of Christ's forerunner

911.definition: [βάπτω] a primary verb; to whelm, i.e. cover wholly with a fluid; in the New Testament only in a qualified or special sense, i.e. (literally) to moisten (a part of one's person), or (by implication) to stain (as with dye)

912.definition: [Βαραββᾶς] of Chaldee origin ({{H1347}} and {{H5}}); son of Abba; Bar-abbas, an Israelite

913.definition: [Βαράκ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1301}}); Barak, an Israelite

914.definition: [Βαραχίας] of Hebrew origin ({{H1296}}); Barachias (i.e. Berechijah), an Israelite

915.definition: [βάρβαρος] of uncertain derivation; a foreigner (i.e. non-Greek)

918.definition: [Βαρθολομαῖος] of Chaldee origin ({{H1247}} and {{H8526}}); son of Tolmai; Bar-tholomæus, a Christian apostle

919.definition: [Βαριησοῦς] of Chaldee origin ({{H1247}} and {{H3091}}); son of Jesus (or Joshua); Bar-jesus, an Israelite

920.definition: [Βαριωνᾶς] of Chaldee origin ({{H1247}} and {{H3124}}); son of Jonas (or Jonah); Bar-jonas, an Israelite

921.definition: [Βαρνάβας] of Chaldee origin ({{H1247}} and {{H5029}}); son of Nabas (i.e. prophecy); Barnabas, an Israelite

922.definition: [βάρος] probably from the same as {{G939}} (through the notion of going down; compare {{G899}}); weight; in the New Testament only, figuratively, a load, abundance, authority

923.definition: [Βαρσαβᾶς] of Chaldee origin ({{H1247}} and probably {{H6634}}); son of Sabas (or Tsaba); Bar-sabas, the name of two Israelites

924.definition: [Βαρτιμαῖος] of Chaldee origin ({{H1247}} and {{H2931}}); son of Timæus (or the unclean); Bar-timæus, an Israelite

926.definition: [βαρύς] from the same as {{G922}}; weighty, i.e. (fig) burdensome, grave

931.definition: [βάσανος] perhaps remotely from the same as {{G939}} (through the notion of going to the bottom); a touch-stone, i.e. (by analogy) torture

932.definition: [βασιλεία] from {{G935}}; properly, royalty, i.e. (abstractly) rule, or (concretely) a realm (literally or figuratively)

935.definition: [βασιλεύς] probably from {{G939}} (through the notion of a foundation of power); a sovereign (abstractly, relatively, or figuratively)

937.definition: [βασιλικός] from {{G935}}; regal (in relation), i.e. (literally) belonging to (or befitting) the sovereign (as land, dress, or a courtier), or (figuratively) preeminent

939.definition: [βάσις] from βαίνω (to walk); a pace ("base"), i.e. (by implication) the foot

940.definition: [βασκαίνω] akin to {{G5335}}; to malign, i.e. (by extension) to fascinate (by false representations)

941.definition: [βαστάζω] perhaps remotely derived from the base of {{G939}} (through the idea of removal); to lift, literally or figuratively (endure, declare, sustain, receive, etc.)

942.definition: [βάτος] of uncertain derivation; a brier shrub

943.definition: [βάτος] of Hebrew origin ({{H1324}}); a bath, or measure for liquids

945.definition: [βαττολογέω] from Βάττος (a proverbial stammerer) and {{G3056}}; to stutter, i.e. (by implication) to prate tediously

948.definition: [βδελύσσω] from a (presumed) derivative of βδέω (to stink); to be disgusted, i.e. (by implication) detest (especially of idolatry)

949.definition: [βέβαιος] from the base of {{G939}} (through the idea of basality); stable (literally or figuratively)

952.definition: [βέβηλος] from the base of {{G939}} and βηλός (a threshold); accessible (as by crossing the door-way), i.e. (by implication, of Jewish notions) heathenish, wicked

954.definition: [Βεελζεβούλ] of Chaldee origin (by parody on {{H1176}}); dung-god; Beelzebul, a name of Satan

955.definition: [Βελίαλ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1100}}); worthlessness; Belial, as an epithet of Satan

956.definition: [βέλος] from {{G906}}; a missile, i.e. spear or arrow

957.definition: [βελτίον] neuter of a compound of a derivative of {{G906}} (used for the comparative of {{G18}}); better

958.definition: [Βενιαμίν] of Hebrew origin ({{H1144}}); Benjamin, an Israelite

959.definition: [Βερνίκη] from a provincial form of {{G5342}} and {{G3529}}; victorious; Bernice, a member of the Herodian family

960.definition: [Βέροια] perhaps a provincial from a derivative of {{G4008}} (Perœa, i.e. the region beyond the coast-line); Berœa, a place in Macedonia

961.definition: [Βεροιαῖος] from {{G960}}; a Berœoean or native of Berœa

962.definition: [Βηθαβαρά] of Hebrew origin ({{H1004}} and {{H5679}}); ferry-house; Bethabara (i.e. Bethabarah), a place on the Jordan

963.definition: [Βηθανία] of Chaldee origin; date-house; Beth-any, a place in Palestine

964.definition: [Βηθεσδά] of Chaldee origin (compare {{H1004}} and {{H2617}}); house of kindness; Beth-esda, a pool in Jerusalem

965.definition: [Βηθλεέμ] of Hebrew origin ({{H1036}}); Bethleem (i.e. Beth-lechem), a place in Palestine

966.definition: [Βηθσαϊδά] of Chaldee origin (compare {{H1004}} and {{H6719}}); fishing-house; Bethsaida, a place in Palestine

967.definition: [Βηθφαγή] of Chaldee origin (compare {{H1004}} and {{H6291}}); fig-house; Beth-phage, a place in Palestine

968.definition: [βῆμα] from the base of {{G939}}; a step, i.e. foot-breath; by implication, a rostrum, i.e. a tribunal

970.definition: [βία] probably akin to {{G979}} (through the idea of vital activity); force

971.definition: [βιάζω] from {{G970}}; to force, i.e. (reflexively) to crowd oneself (into), or (passively) to be seized

976.definition: [βίβλος] properly, the inner bark of the papyrus plant, i.e. (by implication) a sheet or scroll of writing

977.definition: [βιβρώσκω] a reduplicated and prolonged form of an obsolete primary verb (perhaps causative of {{G1006}}); to eat

978.definition: [Βιθυνία] of uncertain derivation; Bithynia, a region of Asia

979.definition: [βίος] a primary word; life, i.e. (literally) the present state of existence; by implication, the means of livelihood

981.definition: [βίωσις] from {{G980}}; living (properly, the act, by implication, the mode)

982.definition: [βιωτικός] from a derivative of {{G980}}; relating to the present existence

984.definition: [βλάπτω] a primary verb; properly, to hinder, i.e. (by implication) to injure

985.definition: [βλαστάνω] from βλαστός (a sprout); to germinate; by implication, to yield fruit

986.definition: [Βλάστος] perhaps the same as the base of {{G985}}; Blastus, an officer of Herod Agrippa

987.definition: [βλασφημέω] from {{G989}}; to vilify; specially, to speak impiously

989.definition: [βλάσφημος] from a derivative of {{G984}} and {{G5345}}; scurrilious, i.e. calumnious (against men), or (specially) impious (against God)

990.definition: [βλέμμα] from {{G991}}; vision (properly concrete; by implication, abstract)

991.definition: [βλέπω] a primary verb; to look at (literally or figuratively) Compare {{G3700}}.

992.definition: [βλητέος] from {{G906}}; fit to be cast (i.e. applied)

993.definition: [Βοανεργές] of Chaldee origin ({{H1123}} and {{H7266}}); sons of commotion; Boanerges, an epithet of two of the apostles

994.definition: [βοάω] apparently a prolonged form of a primary verb; to halloo, i.e. shout (for help or in a tumultuous way)

995.definition: [βοή] from {{G994}}; a halloo, i.e. call (for aid, etc.)

996.definition: [βοήθεια] from {{G998}}; aid; specially, a rope or chain for frapping a vessel

998.definition: [βοηθός] from {{G995}} and theo (to run); a succorer

999.definition: [βόθυνος] akin to {{G900}}; a hole (in the ground); specially, a cistern

1000.definition: [βολή] from {{G906}}; a throw (as a measure of distance)
